mxCell.value: Builds the all the DSUs in the workspace and anchors them to the blockchain
These DSUs can be considered the templates that will be 'instanced'

Upon User Registration on the loader (if that process is not automatic) creates new instance of SSApp (wallet or not) based of provided params. If it's a wallet builds all the apps it contains and mount's them to the wallet

Initializes the SSApp according to it's initialization instructions if any, in this case:
 - create the Id DSU, write the identity info and mount it to /id ;
 - create a constDSU based of the Enterprise Identity and mount the sRead of the ID DSU onto id
 - create a DID from this const DSU (and store it?):
 - create a DSU and mount it to /db to be later fed to the Database code as it;'s base DSU
Core class in PDM's DSU Architecture:
Manages the concept of Enterprise Identity & exposes the DB DSU and Identity to other managers

Manager: 
- Participant DSU: (to be able to recover acccount regardless of wallet. If this responsibility passes to the wallet, this DSU can be removed). All other managers will use this as their root, so whenever you call another manager you are implicitly calling Participant.ManagerX.doSomething()!!!
- Id DSU: mounted to RootDSU/Id this DSU contains the Id data of the participant and can/will be used as a DID for messaging;
- ParticipantConst: Deterministically generated Const DSU, mounted to RootDSU/participant contains, mounted at its '/id' the ReadSSI to the Id DSU. Its this ReadSSI (or a DID version of it) that will be used as 'identity'

Exposes:
- MessageQueue API:
- DB DSU to DB Manager
